Gnathosoma (
Fig. 92
). Infracapitulum covered by anterior prodorsal projection, extending to proximal third of femur I. Palp three-segmented; palp tarsus with two eupathidia, one short and one longer; seta on tibia with serrations; distal segment about one third length of second segment.

Distribution. Azerbaijan , Georgia , Greece , India , Iran , Iraq , Israel , Jordan , Kazakhstan , Spain , Turkey , Ukraine (
